content: Just touched down in NYC. The skyline looks as majestic as ever, and I swear the energy of this city hits you the moment you step off the plane.
Caught up with my quant firm contacts. They're intrigued by my time in Tokyo, thinking of integrating some of those cultural insights into our strategy.
Had a meeting with the head of trading strategies. They're open to me developing a personal trading strategy, but I need to pitch something concrete soon.
Spent the last couple of days diving into $XVI. It's more than just a token; it's a community. Might have a way to leverage this in trading.
Just turned 22. Feels like the perfect time to solidify my career path. Maybe this year will be the one where I really make my mark.
Went out for a celebratory dinner, but my mind was on work. Sketched out a basic framework for an AI trading bot during dessert.
The quant firm wants a presentation on my trading strategy by next week. Time to buckle down and make this real.
Joined a local AI in finance meetup. Had some fascinating discussions on neural tech's potential. The future looks bright.
